body:
I know what the repo README says about these two functions:
> The system tasks $finish, $stop and $display are supported in initial blocks in an unconditional context (only if/case statements on expressions over parameters and constant values are allowed). The intended use for this is synthesis-time DRC.

But I was [comparing Yosys against ISE and Vivado](https://github.com/rodrigomelo9/yosys-versus), using examples provided by Xilinx, and I have a thought to share.

## Example

```
//
// Ignored use of $finish for simulation purposes only
//
// finish_ignored_1.v
//
module finish_ignored_1 (clk, di, do);

  input            clk;
  input      [3:0] di;
  output reg [3:0] do;
  
initial
 begin
  do = 4'b0;
 end
 
always @(posedge clk)
 begin
  if (di < 4'b1100)
    do <= di;
  else
   begin
    $display("%t, di value %d should not be more than 11", $time, di);
    $finish;
   end
 end
 
endmodule
```

What Yosys says:
```
$ yosys -Q -p "read_verilog examples/vivado/finish_ignored.v"

-- Running command `read_verilog examples/vivado/finish_ignored.v' --
ERROR: Can't open input file `examples/vivado/finish_ignored.v' for reading: No such file or directory
ram@ram-notebook2:~/repos/yosys-versus/xilinx$ yosys -Q -p "read_verilog examples/vivado/finish_ignored_1.v"

-- Running command `read_verilog examples/vivado/finish_ignored_1.v' --

1. Executing Verilog-2005 frontend: examples/vivado/finish_ignored_1.v
Parsing Verilog input from `examples/vivado/finish_ignored_1.v' to AST representation.
Generating RTLIL representation for module `\finish_ignored_1'.
examples/vivado/finish_ignored_1.v:0: Warning: System task `$display' outside initial block is unsupported.
examples/vivado/finish_ignored_1.v:0: ERROR: System task `$finish' outside initial block is unsupported.
```

It is the same that happens when `$finish` is inside an initial block within a conditional. Maybe the message could be changed and so `$finish` is supported outside of an initial block? And I suppose that is not difficult to support `$display` also there (where the message is only a warning). Both ISE and Vivado ignore them there, so I think that Yosys has a better solution :-D

This issue can be closed if you evaluated and discarded it in the past, or if you know that is not useful. I am only sharing what I saw making these comparisons.

